01:06:00,680 --> 01:06:03,320
Silent night

702
01:06:03,400 --> 01:06:06,160
Holy night

703
01:06:06,240 --> 01:06:08,880
All is calm

704
01:06:09,000 --> 01:06:11,520
All is bright

705
01:06:11,600 --> 01:06:16,880
Round yon virgin
Mother and child

706
01:06:17,000 --> 01:06:22,360
Holy Infant,
so tender and mild

707
01:06:22,440 --> 01:06:33,760
Sleep in heavenly peace

708
01:06:33,840 --> 01:06:36,600
Silent night

709
01:06:36,680 --> 01:06:39,240
Holy night

710
01:06:39,360 --> 01:06:41,960
All is calm

711
01:06:42,080 --> 01:06:44,800
All is bright

712
01:06:44,920 --> 01:06:50,280
Round yon Virgin
Mother and Child

713
01:06:50,400 --> 01:06:55,640
Holy Infant
so tender and mild

714
01:06:55,760 --> 01:07:01,320
Sleep in heavenly peace

715
01:07:01,440 --> 01:07:06,520
Sleep in heavenly peace

716
01:07:06,640 --> 01:07:09,200
Lovely, Heidi! Lovely.

717
01:07:14,800 --> 01:07:17,240
Merry Christmas
to you all...

718
01:07:17,320 --> 01:07:19,360
and thank you for another
year's faithful service.

719
01:07:19,440 --> 01:07:21,720
Our Christmas greetings to you,
sir, and Fraulein Klara.

720
01:07:21,840 --> 01:07:24,200
A long life
and good health to you both.

721
01:07:24,280 --> 01:07:27,360
- Thank you, Andrews.
- We're very grateful, sir.

722
01:07:27,440 --> 01:07:29,520
- Karl.
- Thank you, sir.

723
01:07:29,640 --> 01:07:31,680
- Fritz.
- Thank you very much, sir.

724
01:07:31,800 --> 01:07:34,360
- Merry Christmas, Frieda.
- Oh, thank you, sir.

725
01:07:34,440 --> 01:07:37,360
We'll wait till
we've had our presents.

726
01:07:37,440 --> 01:07:41,160
He thinks it's going
to be an animal.

727
01:07:41,240 --> 01:07:44,760
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas to you, sir.

728
01:07:44,840 --> 01:07:46,880
For your Christmas,
Fraulein. And thank you...

729
01:07:47,000 --> 01:07:49,680
for the efficient management
of my household.

730
01:07:49,800 --> 01:07:53,200
Thank you, Herr Sesemann.
I've always felt like a mother to Klara.

731
01:07:53,280 --> 01:07:56,000
Now, Papa,
my present to Heidi first.

732
01:07:56,120 --> 01:07:59,520
- Oh, Klara. Your back.
- Oh.

733
01:07:59,640 --> 01:08:01,680
I forgot.

734
01:08:01,800 --> 01:08:03,800
That one, Papa.

735
01:08:07,800 --> 01:08:11,680
- Happy Christmas to you, my dear.
- Thank you.

736
01:08:19,280 --> 01:08:23,120
To Klara,
from her doting papa.

737
01:08:29,080 --> 01:08:32,240
Turn it upside down,
then right-side up, Heidi.

738
01:08:40,400 --> 01:08:43,000
It's the grandfather's house!

739
01:08:43,080 --> 01:08:46,440
He's bringing in the wood.

740
01:08:46,560 --> 01:08:48,520
Can I keep it for always?

741
01:08:48,640 --> 01:08:50,600
Longer than that.

742
01:08:50,680 --> 01:08:53,800
Oh! Heidi, look!

743
01:08:55,400 --> 01:08:58,640
- Oh!
- It's lovely.

744
01:08:58,720 --> 01:09:01,120
Now it's my turn.
I don't see...

745
01:09:01,240 --> 01:09:03,400
my Shetland pony
around anywhere.

746
01:09:03,480 --> 01:09:05,880
Shall we give him
his present now?

747
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:08,240
You hold my doll, Fraulein.

748
01:09:12,000 --> 01:09:15,040
Now watch, Papa.
You stand over there.

749
01:09:24,240 --> 01:09:27,360
- Don't be afraid.
- I'm not.

750
01:09:30,880 --> 01:09:32,800
- Klara, stop!
- Wait!

751
01:09:39,680 --> 01:09:42,720
Lean on me
until you get started.

752
01:09:49,680 --> 01:09:51,240
Now, try hard.

753
01:10:09,680 --> 01:10:12,720
Merry Christmas, Papa.

754
01:10:12,840 --> 01:10:14,840
Oh, my darling.

755
01:10:14,920 --> 01:10:17,240
My darling child.

756
01:10:42,240 --> 01:10:44,880
They told me
you might never walk again.

757
01:10:45,000 --> 01:10:48,560
- How did you? How did it happen?
- Heidi taught me.

758
01:10:48,680 --> 01:10:51,000
Heidi-

759
01:10:53,320 --> 01:10:55,880
I was afraid,
but she made me try.

760
01:10:56,000 --> 01:10:58,080
We did a little more
every day.

761
01:10:58,160 --> 01:11:01,080
You dear child,
you've worked a miracle.

762
01:11:01,160 --> 01:11:03,160
Oh, no. It was the grandfather.

763
01:11:03,280 --> 01:11:05,680
Goat Peter said
I'd never learn to read...

764
01:11:05,760 --> 01:11:07,720
but the grandfather said
I could if I wanted to...

765
01:11:07,840 --> 01:11:09,880
and I did.

766
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:12,160
So I thought Klara
could walk if she wanted to...

767
01:11:12,280 --> 01:11:14,160
and she did.

768
01:11:14,280 --> 01:11:17,480
You've given me the happiest
Christmas of my life.

769
01:11:17,600 --> 01:11:21,160
And I've had a nice
Christmas present too.

770
01:11:21,280 --> 01:11:23,160
Shall I get ready
to go home now?

771
01:11:23,280 --> 01:11:25,680
No. I have another
Christmas present for you-

772
01:11:25,760 --> 01:11:27,920
a home with us
as long as you live.

773
01:11:28,040 --> 01:11:31,160
- No. I couldn't do that.
- Why not?

774
01:11:31,280 --> 01:11:33,240
The grandfather's
been waiting for me...

775
01:11:33,320 --> 01:11:35,280
such a long time.

776
01:11:35,360 --> 01:11:39,160
Oh, Heidi, I hoped
you wouldn't want to go now.

777
01:11:42,640 --> 01:11:44,720
Yes, I'd like to be that...

778
01:11:44,840 --> 01:11:47,640
but I've got to go home.

779
01:11:47,760 --> 01:11:52,000
Papa, I told Heidi you'd
let her go if she wanted to.

780
01:11:52,120 --> 01:11:55,520
But you don't understand, dear.
You'll be my own daughter.

781
01:11:55,600 --> 01:11:58,320
You'll have clothes like Klara's...

782
01:11:58,440 --> 01:12:00,520
everything just like hers...

783
01:12:00,640 --> 01:12:02,520
and grow up to be a great lady.

784
01:12:02,640 --> 01:12:05,440
- Now, wouldn't you like that?
- No, thank you.

785
01:12:05,560 --> 01:12:07,760
I want to go home
to my grandfather.

786
01:12:07,880 --> 01:12:11,360
- I can't let you do that.
- But Klara promised!

787
01:12:11,480 --> 01:12:16,120
- I- - I'm sorry, Heidi.
Someday you'll understand.

788
01:12:22,560 --> 01:12:25,920
Papa, I did promise
you'd send her home.

789
01:12:27,360 --> 01:12:30,240
But dear, you don't know
what her grandfather's like.

790
01:12:30,360 --> 01:12:32,560
Dete told me that he was
a very brutal man...

791
01:12:32,680 --> 01:12:34,560
feared by everyone.

792
01:12:34,680 --> 01:12:38,480
No, Heidi will be
much happier here with us.

793
01:12:43,080 --> 01:12:46,320
You!
You've spoiled everything!

794
01:12:46,400 --> 01:12:48,480
Don't break
my snowstorm!

795
01:12:52,080 --> 01:12:54,120
Fraulein Rottenmeier,!

796
01:12:55,760 --> 01:12:57,680
What is
the meaning of this?

797
01:12:57,760 --> 01:13:00,320
Forgive me, Herr Sesemann,
I- I was beyond myself.

798
01:13:00,440 --> 01:13:04,360
You must realize I cannot
have you longer in my employ.

799
01:13:04,440 --> 01:13:06,920
- Yes, Herr Sesemann.
- I'll give you a month's salary.

800
01:13:07,000 --> 01:13:09,840
You will arrange
to leave tomorrow.

801
01:13:20,560 --> 01:13:23,120
Grandfather.

802
01:13:23,240 --> 01:13:25,960
Grandfather.

803
01:13:27,360 --> 01:13:29,680
I'll never see you again.

804
01:14:02,600 --> 01:14:06,280
- Looking for somebody?
- My granddaughter.

805
01:14:06,400 --> 01:14:08,440
You might find her
at the theater.

806
01:14:08,560 --> 01:14:12,280
Every youngster in town tries
to get there on Christmas day.

807
01:14:12,400 --> 01:14:15,640
Yes. She might be there.
Thank you.

808
01:14:21,800 --> 01:14:25,280
- What is it, Grandpa?
- I'm looking for my granddaughter.

809
01:14:25,400 --> 01:14:29,120
- But you can't go inside.
- I must see if she's here.

810
01:14:29,200 --> 01:14:31,120
Sorry, sir.
The performance is just over.

811
01:14:31,200 --> 01:14:33,120
You better wait over there.

812
01:14:33,200 --> 01:14:35,440
All right.

813
01:14:49,600 --> 01:14:54,440
Santa Claus!

814
01:14:54,560 --> 01:14:59,480
- Santa Claus!
- Santa Claus!

815
01:15:07,600 --> 01:15:10,560
Santa Claus!

816
01:15:10,640 --> 01:15:13,560
Oh, Heidi, see the funny
Santa Claus over there?

817
01:15:13,640 --> 01:15:14,880
Where? I can't see.

818
01:15:15,000 --> 01:15:16,880
Papa, please take us
over to see him.

819
01:15:17,000 --> 01:15:19,800
We better not, dear. You've had
too much excitement for one day.

820
01:15:19,880 --> 01:15:25,120
- But Heidi hasn't seen him.
- Never mind. I don't care.

821
01:15:27,240 --> 01:15:30,400
Heidi!
Heidi, where are you?

822
01:15:30,480 --> 01:15:32,720
It's the grandfather
calling me!

823
01:15:32,840 --> 01:15:35,200
It couldn't be
your grandfather, Heidi.

824
01:15:35,320 --> 01:15:37,760
It sounded just like him.

825
01:15:40,240 --> 01:15:43,400
You must be mistaken, dear. Your grandfather
is 100 miles away on his mountain.

826
01:15:43,480 --> 01:15:47,200
I'm almost sure I heard him.
I know it was his voice!

827
01:15:47,320 --> 01:15:51,360
Grandfather! Grandfather!
Where are you?

828
01:15:51,440 --> 01:15:54,400
Heidi! Heidi!

829
01:16:00,840 --> 01:16:02,960
Whoa!

830
01:16:14,480 --> 01:16:17,200
Don't you worry.
That wasn't your grandfather.

831
01:16:24,080 --> 01:16:26,800
Heidi!
Heidi!

832
01:16:31,160 --> 01:16:33,560
- Heidi!
- What do you want?

833
01:16:33,640 --> 01:16:35,640
I thought this
was the sleigh.

834
01:16:35,760 --> 01:16:37,720
It must be the right street.

835
01:16:37,840 --> 01:16:39,800
Heidi!

836
01:16:39,880 --> 01:16:41,840
Schutzmann,

837
01:16:41,960 --> 01:16:45,000
That old fellow is acting very strangely.
I think you'd better keep an eye on him.

838
01:16:51,640 --> 01:16:55,160
Is my granddaughter here?
A child named Heidi.

839
01:16:55,240 --> 01:16:59,120
Your granddaughter?
It isn't likely.

840
01:16:59,240 --> 01:17:01,120
I'll see for myself!.

841
01:17:01,240 --> 01:17:03,400
Come here!
What are you doing here?

842
01:17:03,520 --> 01:17:07,080
I'm looking for my granddaughter.
She may be in this house!

843
01:17:09,040 --> 01:17:11,440
- Come! Come!
- You better come with us.

844
01:17:11,520 --> 01:17:15,080
She's in one of these houses.
I'll not leave till I find her!

845
01:17:15,200 --> 01:17:19,440
- What is this?
- You can't disturb people!

846
01:17:20,680 --> 01:17:24,080
Herr Wachtmeister,
I heard her cry out from the sleigh.

847
01:17:24,200 --> 01:17:26,080
I tell you,
she's in some trouble.

848
01:17:26,200 --> 01:17:30,200
We can't have you beating on
all the doors of Frankfurt at this hour!

849
01:17:30,320 --> 01:17:33,920
- I must find her.
- Of course. Of course.

850
01:17:34,040 --> 01:17:36,240
But she can come
to no harm tonight.

851
01:17:36,360 --> 01:17:40,160
If you're still worried in the morning,
we'll investigate your story.

852
01:17:40,280 --> 01:17:42,800
I tell you,
I must find her tonight!

853
01:17:43,880 --> 01:17:47,960
- Lock him up.
- The cells are full, Herr Wachtmeister.

854
01:17:48,080 --> 01:17:50,920
Naturally, naturally.
Christmas night.

855
01:17:51,040 --> 01:17:53,760
- Put him in the detention room then.
- But, Herr Wachtmeister-

856
01:17:53,880 --> 01:17:55,960
Take him away.

857
01:18:05,280 --> 01:18:07,800
Stop that.

858
01:18:07,880 --> 01:18:10,040
Christmas comes
but once a year

859
01:18:10,120 --> 01:18:12,360
Ja, and with it
comes too much beer.

860
01:18:14,800 --> 01:18:17,200
christmas comes
but once a year

861
01:18:17,280 --> 01:18:19,880
With it comes
too much beer

862
01:18:51,120 --> 01:18:54,520
Heidi. Get up.

863
01:18:54,640 --> 01:18:56,800
And be very quiet.

864
01:18:56,920 --> 01:18:59,520
Why? What's the matter?

865
01:18:59,640 --> 01:19:02,040
We're going away.

866
01:19:02,120 --> 01:19:05,120
Oh, is it morning already,
and you're going to take me home?

867
01:19:05,240 --> 01:19:07,640
Yes, that's it.
We're going home.

868
01:19:07,720 --> 01:19:09,800
But I thought Andrews
was going to take me.

869
01:19:09,920 --> 01:19:14,200
Shh. He can't. You're to go
with me. Now dress quickly.

870
01:19:21,560 --> 01:19:25,360
If You are
a just and merciful God...

871
01:19:25,480 --> 01:19:27,640
then help me...

872
01:19:27,720 --> 01:19:30,480
in this hour in my need.

873
01:19:31,840 --> 01:19:33,640
Hurry up!

874
01:19:33,720 --> 01:19:36,960
But first I must go and say good-bye
to Klara and her papa.

875
01:19:37,080 --> 01:19:40,640
No, you can't disturb them so early.
I said good-bye for you.

876
01:19:40,720 --> 01:19:42,720
Oh, wait. I forgot.

877
01:19:44,720 --> 01:19:46,880
Don't do that again!

878
01:20:00,120 --> 01:20:03,320
Heidi! Heidi!

879
01:20:22,800 --> 01:20:25,680
I'll put a stop to that.

880
01:20:25,760 --> 01:20:28,160
Ah, let the poor chap
enjoy his Christmas.

881
01:20:30,960 --> 01:20:33,320
Why, it isn't
morning at all.

882
01:20:33,440 --> 01:20:36,160
- It's still night.
- Shh! It's a long way.

883
01:20:36,280 --> 01:20:38,200
You've got to catch
an early train.

884
01:20:51,960 --> 01:20:54,720
- This isn't the right way!
- I know what I'm doing!

885
01:20:54,840 --> 01:20:57,000
I don't think I'll go with you.
I'll wait for Andrews.

886
01:20:57,120 --> 01:20:59,160
He will have to find you first.

887
01:21:06,600 --> 01:21:08,760
Let me go!
Let me go!

888
01:21:25,880 --> 01:21:29,760
- This is the child.
- Ah.

889
01:21:29,880 --> 01:21:31,920
Nice little girl.

890
01:21:33,560 --> 01:21:35,760
Let me go!
I want my grandfather!

891
01:21:35,880 --> 01:21:38,240
- You'll never see your grandfather again.
- Come on!

892
01:21:38,360 --> 01:21:40,960
Come on.
Ayyy!

893
01:21:42,560 --> 01:21:47,160
- Heidi! Heidi!
- Grandfather,! Grandfather,!

894
01:21:47,280 --> 01:21:50,000
Grandfather!
Grandfather!

895
01:21:50,120 --> 01:21:52,640
- Heidi!
- Grandfather,!

896
01:21:52,760 --> 01:21:53,960
Grandfather,
she's hurting me!

897
01:21:56,800 --> 01:21:58,800
Grandfather,
take me home!

898
01:22:03,600 --> 01:22:05,560
What happened?
What's the matter?

899
01:22:08,600 --> 01:22:10,600
That old man stole my child.

900
01:22:10,720 --> 01:22:12,160
Hey, you! Stop!

901
01:22:14,440 --> 01:22:15,160
Stop!

902
01:22:23,640 --> 01:22:26,760
- They've stolen my sled.
- Who owns this one?

903
01:22:26,880 --> 01:22:28,880
- I do.
- Get in, and follow that man.

904
01:22:29,000 --> 01:22:30,880
- What happened?
- Stolen sleigh!

905
01:22:31,000 --> 01:22:32,520
Follow that man
with the child!

906
01:23:47,920 --> 01:23:49,560
Stop!

907
01:23:52,240 --> 01:23:53,880
Stop, or I'll shoot!

908
01:23:55,080 --> 01:23:56,360
Whoa!

909
01:23:57,760 --> 01:23:59,320
You broke out of jail.

910
01:23:59,440 --> 01:24:01,960
You took a sled that
did not belong to you.

911
01:24:02,080 --> 01:24:03,000
You stole that child,!

912
01:24:03,080 --> 01:24:05,680
- He didn't steal me!
- I tell you, she's mine!

913
01:24:05,800 --> 01:24:07,560
Silence!

914
01:24:07,640 --> 01:24:09,400
Herr Captain,
we have found the woman.

915
01:24:09,520 --> 01:24:11,920
Good. Bring her in.

916
01:24:12,040 --> 01:24:14,400
- Is this your child?
- Yes, Herr Captain.

917
01:24:14,480 --> 01:24:15,800
No, I'm not!

918
01:24:15,920 --> 01:24:18,800
Is this the man who struck you
and took her away from you?

919
01:24:18,880 --> 01:24:21,240
- Yes.
- She's lying!

920
01:24:21,360 --> 01:24:25,160
I don't know who she is or what
she's doing, but Heidi is mine!

921
01:24:25,240 --> 01:24:27,760
That's enough!
You will be held for trial.

922
01:24:27,840 --> 01:24:29,680
You stupid fools!

923
01:24:29,800 --> 01:24:33,240
- Can't you see what you're doing?
- Lock him up,!

924
01:24:33,360 --> 01:24:36,480
You can't! You're not going
to take her away from me again!

925
01:24:36,600 --> 01:24:39,000
No! No, you mustn't
take him away!

926
01:24:39,080 --> 01:24:43,080
He's telling the truth!
He is my grandfather.

927
01:24:43,200 --> 01:24:46,760
My really and truly grandfather!
Please! Please let him go!

928
01:24:46,840 --> 01:24:48,760
- Come on! Don't be hysterical.
- Grandfather!

929
01:24:48,840 --> 01:24:51,400
We'll want you for the trial,
Take your child home,

930
01:24:51,520 --> 01:24:54,240
I am not her child!
She's a bad lady!

931
01:24:54,360 --> 01:24:56,320
She tried to sell me
to the Gypsies!

932
01:24:57,840 --> 01:24:59,320
Please.

933
01:24:59,440 --> 01:25:01,640
Please let the grandfather
take me home.

934
01:25:01,760 --> 01:25:04,080
He didn't mean
to do anything bad.

935
01:25:04,200 --> 01:25:06,480
I'll work hard and pay back
for everything he broke.

936
01:25:06,600 --> 01:25:09,520
- So will Swanly and Bearly.
- Pay no attention to her.

937
01:25:09,640 --> 01:25:11,600
She'll be all right
when I get her to bed.

938
01:25:11,680 --> 01:25:14,400
I won't go with her!
She broke my snowstorm...

939
01:25:14,480 --> 01:25:18,520
and sent my Aunt Dete away so she
couldn't take me home to the mountains!

940
01:25:18,640 --> 01:25:22,840
If you don't believe me
just ask Herr Sesemann.

941
01:25:22,960 --> 01:25:28,000
- He'll tell you the truth.
- Herr Sesemann?

942
01:25:28,120 --> 01:25:30,880
What has Herr Sesemann
to do with this?

943
01:25:31,000 --> 01:25:33,840
- Nothing. Nothing at all.
- He has too.

944
01:25:33,960 --> 01:25:36,840
Aunt Dete brought me
there to play with Klara.

945
01:25:36,960 --> 01:25:40,000
- I taught her her how to walk.
- Oh, this is ridiculous.

946
01:25:40,080 --> 01:25:41,680
- Come along.
- Just a minute.

947
01:25:41,800 --> 01:25:45,520
- Well, now, Lieutenant- - Perhaps
we'd better send for Herr Sesemann.

948
01:25:45,640 --> 01:25:49,680
Oh, absurd! We- Well, we visited
the Sesemann house tonight.

949
01:25:49,800 --> 01:25:51,920
Christmas, you know.
My sister's governess there.

950
01:25:52,040 --> 01:25:55,440
It would be highly improper
to disturb Herr Sesemann at this hour!

951
01:25:55,520 --> 01:25:57,480
I think you'd better
wait until we hear...

952
01:25:57,600 --> 01:26:00,680
what Herr Sesemann
has got to say.

953
01:26:00,800 --> 01:26:04,680
Grandfather!
Grandfather!

954
01:26:13,000 --> 01:26:15,960
Dear, dear, dear.

955
01:26:16,080 --> 01:26:20,120
Seems quite impossible.
Nothing emerges from the spigot.

956
01:26:20,240 --> 01:26:22,640
- Not that way!
- Oh.

957
01:26:25,240 --> 01:26:27,160
That way.

958
01:26:27,280 --> 01:26:29,440
My word!

959
01:26:29,560 --> 01:26:34,280
I say, Bearly's
a very warm goat, isn't she?

960
01:26:34,400 --> 01:26:38,440
- Of course, silly. All goats are warm.
- How cozy.

961
01:26:38,560 --> 01:26:41,640
Heidi,! Heidi,!
They're coming,!

962
01:26:41,720 --> 01:26:43,960
Really ought to master this.

963
01:26:48,560 --> 01:26:50,960
Let's have a race
to the grandfather.

964
01:26:56,280 --> 01:26:58,360
Well, well.

965
01:26:58,480 --> 01:27:00,440
Oh, Grandfather, this is Klara.

966
01:27:00,560 --> 01:27:03,240
And just think-
she beat me running!

967
01:27:03,320 --> 01:27:05,560
And I beat Herr Sesemann.

968
01:27:05,680 --> 01:27:07,880
How do you do?

969
01:27:07,960 --> 01:27:11,000
This is the grandmother
and Goat Peter.

970
01:27:12,040 --> 01:27:14,560
And this is Pastor Schultz
and Frau Schultz.

971
01:27:14,680 --> 01:27:16,720
I guess I can't deny it this time.

972
01:27:16,840 --> 01:27:18,600
They were married yesterday.

973
01:27:18,720 --> 01:27:20,800
Come, sit down, all of you!

974
01:27:20,880 --> 01:27:24,040
You must be starved
after your climb up the mountain.

975
01:27:26,840 --> 01:27:29,400
Bless us, O Lord,
in these Thy gifts...

976
